Picture of the day

Image of the Virgin of Los Remedios Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virgin_of_Los_Remedios ("Lady of the Cures") in the homonymous Baroque Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baroque chapel of the church of John the Baptist Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_the_Baptist , Ágreda, province of Soria, Image of the Virgin of Los Remedios Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virgin_of_Los_Remedios ("Lady of the Cures") in the homonymous Baroque Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baroque chapel of the church of John the Baptist Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_the_Baptist Castile and León, Spain. The chapel was built in 1697 by Count of Villarea. The originally Romanesque church (visible in its portal) was built in the second half of the 12th century and reworked in the 16th century with Gothic , Renaissance and Baroque elements, while the reredos behind the image dates from the 18th century.

Media of the day

Play media Link: https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/51/BlackBerry_Leap-sensores_array_infrared_proximity-I3200_VNr%C2%B00003.webm

The pulsing proximity sensor Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proximity_sensor of a BlackBerry Leap Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BlackBerry_Leap during a call. It detects when it is covered and turns off the smartphone screen. The sensor size is about 1.5 by 1.5 mm.

Participating

Log in Link: /wiki/Special:UserLogin Create account Link: /wiki/Special:UserLogin/signup

Browsing?
Please use the search box at the top of this page or the links to the right. Feel free to subscribe to our syndicated feeds Link: /wiki/Commons:Feeds .
Using?
To fulfill the free license requirements, please read our Reuse Link: /wiki/Commons:Reusing_content_outside_Wikimedia guide. You can also request a picture Link: /wiki/Commons:Picture_requests .
Identifying?
Have a browse through Category:Unidentified subjects Link: /wiki/Category:Unidentified_subjects . If you find something you can identify, write a note on the item's talk page.
Creating?
Check out all you need to know at our Contributing your own work Link: /wiki/Commons:Contributing_your_own_work guide.
and more!
To explore more ways you can contribute to this project, check out the Community Portal Link: /wiki/Commons:Community_portal .

Monthly photo challenge

Take some photos and upload them to meet our monthly thematic challenge, get inspiration and try new subjects! Learn more about the challenges! Link: /wiki/Commons:Photo_challenge

Check out this month's challenges Link: /wiki/Commons:Photo_challenge#Challenges_open_for_submission

Highlights

If you are browsing Commons for the first time, you may want to start with Featured pictures Link: /wiki/Commons:Featured_pictures , Quality images Link: /wiki/Commons:Quality_images , Valued images Link: /wiki/Commons:Valued_images or Featured videos Link: /wiki/Commons:Featured_videos . You can also see some work created by our highly skilled contributors in Meet our photographers Link: /wiki/Commons:Meet_our_photographers and Meet our illustrators Link: /wiki/Commons:Meet_our_illustrators . You may also be interested in Picture of the Year Link: /wiki/Commons:Picture_of_the_Year .
